President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Dr. John N. Nkengasong as Ambassador-at-Large and Coordinator of United States Government Activities to Combat HIV/AIDS Globally at the Department of State. This role involves leading and overseeing the President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR), which is the largest commitment by any nation to address a single disease in history. Dr. Nkengasong, currently the Director of the Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention, would be the first person of African origin to hold this position if confirmed. He has a strong background in public health, including previous roles at the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and extensive experience in HIV/AIDS and epidemic preparedness. Dr. Nkengasong is a U.S. citizen and has received numerous awards for his work.